title: Google\Cloud\WebSecurityScanner\V1beta\ScanConfig
name: ScanConfig
description:
A ScanConfig resource contains the configurations to launch a scan.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.websecurityscanner.v1beta.ScanConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The resource name of the ScanConfig. The name follows the format of 'projects/{projectId}/scanConfigs/{scanConfigId}'. The ScanConfig IDs are generated by the system.

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: Required. The user provided display name of the ScanConfig.

params.name: data.max_qps
params.description: The maximum QPS during scanning. A valid value ranges from 5 to 20 inclusively. If the field is unspecified or its value is set 0, server will default to 15. Other values outside of [5, 20] range will be rejected with INVALID_ARGUMENT error.

params.name: data.starting_urls
params.description: Required. The starting URLs from which the scanner finds site pages.

params.name: data.authentication
params.description: The authentication configuration. If specified, service will use the authentication configuration during scanning.

params.name: data.user_agent
params.description: The user agent used during scanning.

params.name: data.blacklist_patterns
params.description: The blacklist URL patterns as described in https://cloud.google.com/security-scanner/docs/excluded-urls

params.name: data.schedule
params.description: The schedule of the ScanConfig.

params.name: data.target_platforms
params.description: Set of Cloud Platforms targeted by the scan. If empty, APP_ENGINE will be used as a default.

params.name: data.export_to_security_command_center
params.description: Controls export of scan configurations and results to Cloud Security Command Center.

params.name: data.latest_run
params.description: Latest ScanRun if available.

params.name: data.risk_level
params.description: The risk level selected for the scan
